Create a production-ready wrapper component with the following characteristics:

Name: LazyMotionWrapper
Description: A wrapper component for using motion animations with Framer Motion from within a client side rendered React application. Use it when you want to add animations to your UI components without a full rebuild of the page. This component uses the DOM as the source of truth for its animations.
Style: modern
Interactions: animated
Tags: animation, framer-motion, client-side-rendering

Requirements:
- Works in React with TypeScript by default but adaptable to Vue, Svelte, or plain HTML/CSS
- Uses Tailwind CSS for styling
- Fully accessible with ARIA labels and keyboard navigation
- Responsive and mobile-friendly
- No external dependencies beyond React and Tailwind unless necessary
- Include all necessary imports
- Export as default with sensible prop types

Generate clean production-ready code only. No explanations.
Reference implementation (adapt don't copy):
// components/LazyMotionWrapper.tsx
"use client";

import { LazyMotion, domAnimation } from "framer-motion";
import { ReactNode } from "react";

export default ({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) => (
  <LazyMotion features={domAnimation}>{children}</LazyMotion>
);
